A: The problem is that you are trying to create a directory in the Download folder, not in the sdcard.
You should use Environment.getExternalStorageDirectory() instead of "/sdcard".
Also, you should check if the directory was created successfully.
Here is the corrected code:
public void save(View view) {
    myImage.setDrawingCacheEnabled(true);
    Bitmap imgV = myImage.getDrawingCache();
    String root = Environment.getExternalStorageDirectory().toString();
    File myDir = new File(root + "/AVP_saved");
    myDir.mkdirs(); // Create the directory if it doesn't exist
    String fname="Image.png";
    File file = new File(myDir, fname);
    try {
        FileOutputStream out = new FileOutputStream(file);
        imgV.compress(Bitmap.CompressFormat.PNG, 90, out);
        out.flush();
        out.close();
        Toast.makeText(this, "Image Downloaded", Toast.LENGTH_LONG).show();
    } catch (Exception e) {
        e.printStackTrace();
        Toast.makeText(this, e.getMessage(), Toast.LENGTH_LONG).show();
    }
}

This code will create a directory named "AVP_saved" in the root of your external storage (usually /sdcard). If the directory already exists, this method will do nothing.
Also, note that you should use Toast.LENGTH_LONG instead of 7000 and 8000, because these are not valid parameters for the duration.

A: You can use the following code to create a directory if it does not exist:
File dir = new File(Environment.getExternalStorageDirectory() + "/AVP_saved");
if (!dir.exists()) {
    dir.mkdirs();
}

This code will create a directory named "AVP_saved" in the root of your external storage (usually /sdcard). If the directory already exists, this method will do nothing.

